I"u<h4 id="method">Method</h4>

<p><strong>step 1</strong>: prepare the dataset <br /></p>
<ol>
  <li>create bibliography file with extension name “bib”, such as <strong>citation-database.bib</strong></li>
  <li>find the paper you need in google scholar</li>
  <li>click <strong>Import into BibTex</strong> link, and copy the source code to the bibliography file.</li>
</ol>

<div class="language-latex highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>@article<span class="p">{</span>liu2015comparison,
  title=<span class="p">{</span>Comparison of four Adaboost algorithm based artificial neural networks in wind speed predictions<span class="p">}</span>,
  author=<span class="p">{</span>Liu, Hui and Tian, Hong-qi and Li, Yan-fei and Zhang, Lei<span class="p">}</span>,
  journal=<span class="p">{</span>Energy Conversion and Management<span class="p">}</span>,
  volume=<span class="p">{</span>92<span class="p">}</span>,
  pages=<span class="p">{</span>67--81<span class="p">}</span>,
  year=<span class="p">{</span>2015<span class="p">}</span>,
  publisher=<span class="p">{</span>Elsevier<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

</code></pre></div></div>

<p><strong>step 2</strong>: include the <strong>citation-database.bib</strong> file, without the extension</p>
<ol>
  <li>There are a couple of reference style.
    <ul>
      <li>plain</li>
      <li>unsrt</li>
      <li>ieeetr</li>
      <li>alpha</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="language-latex highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">\bibliographystyle</span><span class="p">{</span>plain<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="k">\bibliography</span><span class="p">{</span>citation-database<span class="p">}</span>
<span class="nt">\end{document}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><strong>step 3</strong>: cite in the paper <br />
The grammar is pretty simple</p>

<div class="language-latex highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>According to the paper<span class="k">\cite</span><span class="p">{</span>liu2015comparison<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

